  "commentary": "With SPX at 6563.94 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-16.9B) and max positive gamma at 6580 (+11.5B), dealers are likely buying aggressively here as spot hovers just above the largest amplifying level. The BREAKOUT regime with -28.2B total GEX means dealers will continue momentum trades - buying any push toward 6580 and selling hard if we break back below 6550. Watch 6580 as the critical flip point where dealer flow reverses from buying to selling, while 6550 remains the key support where maximum buying pressure kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 and 6580 with potential for explosive moves on any breakout from this range.",
